title: Mount Ulap
shortDescription: One of the most famous hikes in Benguet is Mt Ulap in Itogon.
description: Mount Ulap is a 7.7 kilometer moderately trafficked point-to-point trail located near Tuba, Banguat, Philippines that offers the chance to see wildlife and is rated as moderate. The trail is primarly used for hiking.

title: Calaguas Islands
shortDescription: A paradise of islands that can rival the white sand beauty of Boracay.
description: Calaguas, also known as Calaguas Islands, is a group of islands located in the Philippine province of Camarines Norte. It includes the major islands of Tinaga Island and Guintinua Island, the minor Maculabo Island, as well as several other minor. The group of islands is around 200 km away from the capital city of Manila and can be accessed through the ports at Paracale and Daet, Camarines Norte.

title: Onay Beach
shortDescription: This is one of the best beach camping sites, beautiful and pristine.
description: Locals call this place Onay Beach. The prized possession of Brgy. Onay (Doa Luisa), this golden beach is the most popular swimming spot in the island of Laoang, located a couple of minutes off the coast of the north-eastern tip of Northern Samar. Blanketed in a glowing mixture of white, black, and brown grains, Onay Beach reflects the afternoon sun and glitter as if the sand is golden.

title: Seven Sisters Waterfall
shortDescription: The Seven Sisters is the 39th tallest waterfall in Norway.
description: The Seven Sisters (Norwegian: De Syv Sstrene or Dei sju systrene, also known as Knivsflfossen) is the 39th tallest waterfall in Norway. The 410-metre (1,350 ft) tall waterfall consists of seven separate streams, and the tallest of the seven has a free fall that measures 250 metres (820 ft). The waterfall is located along the Geirangerfjorden in Stranda Municipality in Mre og Romsdal county, Norway. The waterfall is located just south of the historic Knivsfl farm, across the fjord from the old Skagefl farm. The falls are about 6.5 kilometres (4.0 mi) west of the village of Geiranger. It is part of the Geiranger World Heritage Site.

title: Latik Riverside
shortDescription: Philippines is one of the most dazzling countries in all of Asia.
description: Nestled between the Wet Mountains and the Sangre de Cristo Range are the scenic towns of Westcliffe and Silver Cliff.  The Wet Mountain Valley is a peaceful home for residents and a glorious get-a-way for the thousands of visitors who discover this well-kept secret each year. The majestic peaks of the Sangre de Cristo Mountains provide a panoramic backdrop for the area, with nine of the states 54 fourteen thousand foot peaks  in proximinity.

title: Buloy Springs
shortDescription: This is one of the best beach camping sites, beautiful and pristine.
description: With more than 7,000 islands consisting of rice paddies, volcanos, hills, mountains, cliffs, world-class surf spots, and endemic wildlife, the Philippines is one of the most dazzling and diverse countries in all of Asia. Not to mention, its home to some of the worlds best beaches, too. The country is a biodiversity hotspot, having the worlds highest endemism rate for bird species, and one of the highest for mammals and flora.
